Package: replicateEverything
Title: Tools to Replicate Empirical Research Papers
Version: 0.7.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Macartan", "Humphreys", email = "macartan.humphreys@wzb.eu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Cord", "Masche", email = "cord.masche@wzb.eu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Vermon", "Washington", email = "vermon.washington@wzb.eu", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Provides tools for discovering and running computational replications of
    empirical research papers. The package connects to a replication registry, retrieves
    replication materials (data, code, and metadata), and reproduces figures and tables
    from published studies in a standardized workflow. Includes a bundled Shiny demo
    app (live demo at <https://shiny2.wzb.eu/ipi/replicate/>; also
    `run_shiny_app()`, `save_local_shiny()`).
